    <item>
      <title>3D plots as in Mathematica</title>
      <link>/post/3d-plots-as-in-mathematica/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 20 May 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/post/3d-plots-as-in-mathematica/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes you just need to visualize a shape of a function. Ideally this should be fast, intuitive and simple. I always liked the simplicity of Wolfram Mathematica 3D plots. Just do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-mathematica&#34; data-lang=&#34;mathematica&#34;&gt;Plot3D[Sin[x&lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;y],&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bbb&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;{x,&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bbb&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bbb&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;},&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bbb&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;{y,&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bbb&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bbb&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#666&#34;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;}]&lt;span style=&#34;color:#bbb&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;and you have a very nice plot. Which is, by the way, interactive (as long as you stay in Mathematica)&lt;/p&gt;
